{
  "text": "In order to investigate different phylogenetic questions, assess levels of correspondence among the different phylogenetic markers, and derive the most robust phylogenetic hypothesis of Trachylina possible, we created five datasets. First, partial mitochondrial 16S, nuclear SSU, and nuclear LSU data for all taxa (Table 1) were aligned using MUSCLE (multiple sequence alignment with high accuracy and high throughput) [CITATION_1] . No adjustments were made by eye. 'Conserved' positions for each of the alignments were identified using Gblocks v0.91 [CITATION_2] with default parameters, except that half the taxa were allowed to be gaps for any given position. Positions deemed non-conserved by Gblocks were excluded from phylogenetic analysis.",
